<div class="header">
  <div class="eyebrow">Department of History &amp; Political Science · FAMU · Vol. 1, No. 2</div>
  <h1>PSSA Department Blast</h1>
  <div class="byline">Prof. Jonathan Blackmon and Dr. Abdul Sharif</div>
  <div class="tagline">Jobs, Internships, Fellowships, Organizations, Deadlines — curated for you every 2 to 4 weeks.</div>
</div>

<!-- ── INTRO ── -->
<div class="intro">
  <p><strong>We heard you.</strong> A number of you reached out after the last blast asking for more political campaigning and electoral roles — the kind of work that puts you on the ground inside a real campaign. Prof. Blackmon and Dr. Sharif heard that, and this drop reflects it. You will find a dedicated section on political organizing and campaigns this issue, and we will keep building in that direction.</p>
  <p>As always, this blast covers the full range of tracks: federal and state government, pre-law, civil rights, think tanks, and conservation. Not every opportunity is for every student. Scan for what fits your moment, move fast on anything with a hard deadline, and keep an eye on the Watch List at the bottom for what is opening next cycle.</p>
  <p><strong>Have something to share?</strong> If you come across a listing, fellowship, or event that belongs in the next blast, send it our way. We want this to be a two-way street.</p>
</div>


<!-- ── SECTION: POLITICAL ORGANIZING & CAMPAIGNS ── -->
<div class="section">
  <div class="section-label">Political Organizing &amp; Campaigns</div>

  <div class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--green);">
    <div class="card-title">North Carolina Democratic Party — Multiple Campaign Roles</div>
    <div class="card-meta">
      <span class="tag tag-open">Open Now</span>
      <span class="tag tag-paid">Paid · Multiple Positions</span>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Raleigh, NC and statewide.</strong> This one came directly from Dr. Eno, and it is worth your full attention. The NCDP is actively hiring across their 2026 Coordinated Campaign — field organizers, campus organizing fellows, voter access fellows, regional organizing directors, and more. These are real campaign infrastructure roles, not coffee-and-copies internships. If you want to understand how a statewide Democratic operation works from the inside — voter contact, volunteer management, coalition building, ballot access — this is it.</p>
    <p>North Carolina is one of the most competitive battleground states heading into 2026, which means this is high-stakes, high-learning work. Roles currently posted include: <strong>Field Organizer, Campus Organizing Fellowship, Voter Access Fellow, Regional Organizing Director, Impact Organizer, Impact Fellow,</strong> and several director-level positions. Browse the full list and apply directly.</p>
    <a href="https://www.ncdp.org/work-with-us/" target="_blank">Browse All NCDP Openings →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">Fall 2026 Paid Internship, Students for Voting Justice</div>
    <div class="card-meta">
      <span class="tag tag-rolling">Rolling Until Filled</span>
      <span class="tag tag-paid">$16.50/hr · Remote · 5–10 hrs/week</span>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Remote · August 28 – November 5, 2026.</strong> Focused on mobilizing Black voters in rural Georgia and North Carolina — two states where margins matter enormously in 2026. You will be trained in digital political marketing, volunteer leadership, and strategic voter outreach. Genuine field-facing campaign work done remotely at a competitive hourly rate. Strong fit for students interested in electoral organizing who want real experience before graduation.</p>
    <a href="https://www.studentsforvotingjustice.org/apply" target="_blank">Apply at studentsforvotingjustice.org →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">Program Coordinator, Engage Miami</div>
    <div class="card-meta">
      <span class="tag tag-rolling">Rolling</span>
      <span class="tag tag-paid">Part-Time · Central Florida</span>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Central Florida.</strong> Engage Miami is hiring a Program Coordinator to lead 2026 campus and community engagement: managing fellows, tabling, canvassing, phone banking, event organizing, and coordinating student trips to Tallahassee. A part-time, on-the-ground organizing role well suited for a student who wants to build civic engagement skills while staying in Florida. To apply, email a resume and a 5–7 sentence statement of interest.</p>
    <a href="mailto:hiring@engage.miami" target="_blank">Email hiring@engage.miami →</a>
  </div>

  <div class="card">
    <div class="card-title">Internships, Democratic National Committee</div>
    <div class="card-meta">
      <span class="tag tag-rolling">Check for Current Cycle</span>
      <span class="tag tag-paid">Washington, DC</span>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Washington, DC.</strong> The DNC runs internship cycles with placements in grassroots organizing, events, communications, and political operations. Fellows get direct exposure to national party infrastructure and networking with Democratic Party leadership. Check the portal for the current cycle and application window.</p>
    <a href="https://democrats.org/internships/" target="_blank">Apply at democrats.org →</a>
  </div>

</div>


